This is a harmless sleep disorder called somnilokvie.
It is very common, especially in children and adolescents.
Certainly no one of you was told that at night he spoke out of sleep.
This phenomenon can occur very sporadically (for example, once in a lifetime with high fever), or with greater regularity (every day, once a week, once a few months...), the next day the child doesn’t remember anything.
There is not only one reason to explain its occurrence.
It is often associated with other sleep disorders, such as nightmares, nightmares, enuresis nocturna (night aiding) or meshness, but it may not be so.
