In cases when it manifests with great strength, it would be advisable to observe the child and consult with a specialist to find out if he has any problem that causes great anxiety and thus manifests himself.
We have said that it is a harmless disorder, therefore it is not treated only if it is associated with another sleep disorder that can be treated (for example, if it is associated with apnea syndrome or permanent stress).
However, we can do this by remembering a few very simple preventive measures, such as:
Try not to disturb the child before he goes to sleep.
