The bill on a $700 billion economy rescue package, which is to be divided into several payments and aimed at the recovery of bank loans of poor quality, has already written form.
In the first round, half of the amount will be used.
After further talks, which ended until Saturday after midnight US Eastern Time, Congress officials reached an agreement in a few days-long debate on a $700 billion rescue package, Reuters said.
“We’ve made significant progress,” said Nancy Pelosi, the Democratic Chairman of the House of Representatives, saying that only the agreement remains to be signed.
The package was also supported by both presidential candidates Barack Obama and John McCain.
Finance Minister Henry Paulson on the result of the compromise stated: "The program will work and will be effective, but further steps must be taken."
The written form of the package was published before the Asian markets opened on Sunday at 8 p.m. in the evening of Washington time (i.e. on Monday at 2 p.m. in the morning of Central European time), but it did not cause any special rise on the stock exchanges.
The draft legal standard, which is called the 2008 Emergency Economic Stabilization Act, which the programme is to set up, will be voted first by the House of Representatives on Monday, then the seat will be in the Senate.
President George W. Bush spoke with Pelosi on Saturday evening, after the news of the deal was also welcomed in the White House.
“We are satisfied with the progress that was made tonight and we appreciate both sides’ efforts to stabilize our financial markets and protect our economy,” White House spokesman Tony Fratto said.
The program differs from the original proposal of the Bush administration, in which it was intended to spend a total of $700 billion at once on the purchase of low-quality securities secured by mortgages.
Now it is possible to spend in the first round a maximum half of the amount of 700 billion, so that 250 billion will be used immediately after the matter as expected will be decided by Congress on Monday, and the Ministry of Finance will buy for them securities secured by mortgages, which are assessed as poor, the fate of the remaining $100 billion then will depend on the decision of the President.
The program will be controlled by a special body, a member of which will also be the chairman of the Federal Reserve Bank.
The second half of $700 billion will depend on the next decision of Congress.
The Ministry of Finance may, in the sense of the law, apply a combined tactic: it may at the same time buy low-quality loans, mortgages and securities secured by mortgages, respectively, other "toxic" loans.
The purchase can also be carried out in the framework of the auctions and directly, the competent representatives of the ministry said.
The legal standard will allow the companies concerned to participate in the insurance program, in which the Ministry of Finance will provide them with a guarantee on funds that are a reason for concern, for which then the companies will pay the price corresponding to the amount of expected damages.
As Henry Paulson said, the law provides the necessary funds to spend up to $700 billion to meet the urgent requirements of the U.S. financial system, whether it is a large-scale purchase of bad funds, their insurance or the prevention of the systemic risk associated with the collapse of any of the major monetary institutions.
“We will take the necessary steps to be prepared to introduce the law as soon as it is signed,” he added.
The chiefs of the banks, who have come into trouble and are waiting for the aid of the state, can, on the contrary, count on the fact that the government will reduce their departure fees - which in the overseas slang is simply called "the golden paddle".
The limitation of their remuneration will only occur in certain cases, in addition, these limitations will depend on the way of assistance provided by the Ministry.
The limitation in essence means that if the ministry will shop in the framework of the auction, a tax allowance will be imposed on the golden paddles, unless the bank directors will be sent directly into retirement.
In the case of a direct purchase of low-quality loans, the government will aggressively proceed in order to ensure that money for the leadership is not exaggerated.
It should be added that the already existing gold paddles contracts will not change, the limitation applies only to new contracts, which is to be another incentive to participate in the program.
“This is the first case in U.S. history when a legal restriction on the remuneration of the Chief Executive Officer will be in force,” said Barney Frank, President of the House of Representatives’ Financial Services Committee.
Furthermore, the state will have the right to gain a share in the program-participating banks, thereby reducing the risk of taxpayers, since once the economy and the rescued bank stands on their feet, they can also earn on this transaction.
The draft plan includes that in the next five years the President must submit a proposal to the Congress to determine how taxpayers can reimburse the expected losses from the financial sector.
Of course, there were also votes on both sides in connection with the plan of doubt.
“This is what the American citizens did not ask us, this is what the taxpayer’s dollars will not protect,” said Darrell Issa, a Republican congressman from California.
His Democratic colleague from Ohia Mary Kaptur judges that the provisions were urged by exactly those responsible for the collapse of Wall Street.
